#diseaseDefinitionsModal(tabindex="-1", role="dialog", aria-labelledby="myModalLabel", aria-hidden="true").modal.fade
  .modal-dialog
    .modal-content
      .modal-header
        button(type="button", data-dismiss="modal").close
          span(aria-hidden="true") &times;
          span.sr-only Close
        h4#myModalLabel.modal-title Concept Definitions

      .modal-body
        .panel
          .panel-body
            p.lead <span style='background-color:rgb(209, 243, 255);'>Disease</span> concepts include:
            ol(style='margin-left: 8px;').list-unstyled
              li <strong>Disease</strong> – a particular abnormal, pathological condition that affects part or all of an organism
              li <strong>Disease Class</strong> – a specific category of similar but different diseases
              li <strong>Symptom</strong> – the physical manifestations of a disease
              li <strong>Signs/diagnostic signs</strong> – symptoms or test results that support a disease diagnosis. These generally exclude genetic tests, which often define (as opposed to support) a disease diagnosis.
              p <br>When in doubt, search online resources like: <a href='http://www.diseasesdatabase.com/begin.asp' target='_blank'>http://www.diseasesdatabase.com/begin.asp</a> and <a href='http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh/' target='_blank'>http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh/</a> or visit our <a href='http://mark2cure.wikia.com/wiki/Board:Diseases_Concept_Help' target='_blank'>new Wikia forum for help</a>.

      .modal-footer
        button(type="button", data-dismiss="modal").btn.btn-default Close
